#### [NEW] [TaxCalculationServiceTest.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/inertia/tests/Feature/TaxCalculator/TaxCalculationServiceTest.php)

**Tests `TaxCalculationService` — the core tax math engine**

| # | Test Case |
|---|---|
| 1 | `allocateIncome` — proportional allocation (100k, 200 days → 54,795) |
| 2 | `allocateIncome` — full year (365 days → full income) |
| 3 | `calculateForCountry` — flat tax country (e.g. 15% rate) |
| 4 | `calculateForCountry` — progressive tax with 3 brackets |
| 5 | `calculateForCountry` — custom percentage tax type (e.g. 5% social security) |
| 6 | `calculateForCountry` — custom flat amount tax type (e.g. $1,500 annual) |
| 7 | `calculateForCountry` — mixed: income tax brackets + custom override on social security |
| 8 | `calculateForCountry` — no brackets and no flat rate → $0 tax |
| 9 | `calculateForCountry` — bracket with cap (`has_cap=true`, `annual_cap=5000`) |
| 10 | `calculateForCountry` — zero income → $0 tax, 0% effective rate |

---

#### [NEW] [ResidencyDeterminationTest.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/inertia/tests/Feature/TaxCalculator/ResidencyDeterminationTest.php)

**Tests `ResidencyDeterminationService`**

| # | Test Case |
|---|---|
| 1 | 200 days in 183-threshold country → tax resident |
| 2 | 100 days in 183-threshold country → NOT tax resident |
| 3 | Exactly 183 days → tax resident |
| 4 | Country where `counts_arrival_day=false` reduces effective days by 1 |
| 5 | Country where `counts_departure_day=false` reduces effective days by 1 |
| 6 | Both arrival/departure not counted → reduces by 2 |
| 7 | `generateWarnings` — near threshold (within 14 days) produces warning |
| 8 | `generateWarnings` — barely resident produces warning |
| 9 | `generateWarnings` — far from threshold → no warning |

---

#### [NEW] [TreatyResolutionTest.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/inertia/tests/Feature/TaxCalculator/TreatyResolutionTest.php)

**Tests `TreatyResolutionService`**

| # | Test Case |
|---|---|
| 1 | No treaty between countries → no adjustment |
| 2 | `credit` treaty → 15% reduction on tax |
| 3 | `exemption` treaty for non-resident → tax becomes $0 |
| 4 | `exemption` treaty for tax resident → NOT applied (skipped) |
| 5 | `partial` treaty → 50% reduction |
| 6 | Same country as citizenship → no treaty lookup |

---

#### [NEW] [FeieCalculationTest.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/inertia/tests/Feature/TaxCalculator/FeieCalculationTest.php)

**Tests `FeieCalculationService`**

| # | Test Case |
|---|---|
| 1 | Non-US citizen → returns `null` |
| 2 | US citizen, 340 days outside → eligible, income excluded |
| 3 | US citizen, 300 days outside → NOT eligible |
| 4 | US citizen, income > FEIE limit → exclusion capped at limit |
| 5 | US citizen, income < FEIE limit → full income excluded |

---

#### [NEW] [FullPipelineTest.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/inertia/tests/Feature/TaxCalculator/FullPipelineTest.php)

**End-to-end tests through `TaxCalculatorService::calculateTaxes()`**

| # | Test Case |
|---|---|
| 1 | Single country, flat tax — calculates correct total |
| 2 | Two countries, progressive + flat — income allocated proportionally |
| 3 | One country resident + one non-resident — only resident is taxed |
| 4 | With custom taxes (percentage + flat) — adds to total |
| 5 | US citizen with FEIE eligibility — adjusts US tax downward |
| 6 | Treaty between citizenship and residence country — applies credit |

